User: hirayama  Sat Apr 29 09:57:05 PDT 2006
timeSystem/src/test

Modified Files:
	test_timeSystem.cxx 
Log Message:
Debugged AbsoluteTime and revised a test code to reveal them. The bugs are:
[Bug1] Comparison of AbsoluteTimes may be incorrect in UTC,
       because m_time + m_origin may not result in a correct MJD,
       and because m_origin and other.m_origin may be different.
[Bug2] Subtraction of AbsoluteTimes may be incorrect in UTC,
       because m_origin - since.m_origin may not result in a correct
       time difference.
[Note on Bugs 1 and 2] Buggy arithmetic on m_origin can be found in
       comparison operators and AbsoluteTime::computeElapsedTime method,
       and nowhere else.
[Bug3] Conversion from TAI to UTC is wrong when the origin of the TAI
       time is during a leap second, where the time difference between
       them becomes a non-integral number of seconds.

    *
------------------------------------------------------------
